\mt1 Genesis  
\c 1  
\p
\v 1 \w In|strong="H8064"\w* \w the|strong="H1254"\w* \w beginning|strong="H7225"\w* \w God|strong="H8064"\w* \w created|strong="H1254"\w* \w the|strong="H1254"\w* \w heavens|strong="H8064"\w* \w and|strong="H8064"\w* \w the|strong="H1254"\w* \w earth|strong="H8064"\w*.  
\v 2 \w The|strong="H6440"\w* earth \w was|strong="H1961"\w* \w formless|strong="H8414"\w* \w and|strong="H6440"\w* \w empty|strong="H8414"\w*, \w and|strong="H6440"\w* \w darkness|strong="H2822"\w* covered \w the|strong="H6440"\w* \w surface|strong="H6440"\w* \w of|strong="H6440"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* \w deep|strong="H8415"\w*. \w The|strong="H6440"\w* \w Spirit|strong="H7307"\w* \w of|strong="H6440"\w* God \w moved|strong="H7307"\w* \w over|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* \w surface|strong="H6440"\w* \w of|strong="H6440"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* \w waters|strong="H4325"\w*.   
\p
\v 3 God said, “\w Let|strong="H1961"\w* \w there|strong="H1961"\w* \w be|strong="H1961"\w* light!” \w and|strong="H1961"\w* \w there|strong="H1961"\w* \w was|strong="H1961"\w* light.  
\v 4 God \w saw|strong="H7200"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w the|strong="H7200"\w* light \w was|strong="H2896"\w* \w good|strong="H2896"\w*, \w and|strong="H7200"\w* \w he|strong="H3588"\w* separated \w the|strong="H7200"\w* light \w from|strong="H7200"\w* \w the|strong="H7200"\w* \w darkness|strong="H2822"\w*.  
\v 5 God \w called|strong="H7121"\w* \w the|strong="H3117"\w* light “\w day|strong="H3117"\w*,” \w and|strong="H3117"\w* \w he|strong="H3117"\w* \w called|strong="H7121"\w* \w the|strong="H3117"\w* \w darkness|strong="H2822"\w* “\w night|strong="H3915"\w*.” \w So|strong="H1961"\w* \w there|strong="H1961"\w* \w was|strong="H1961"\w* \w evening|strong="H6153"\w*, \w and|strong="H3117"\w* \w then|strong="H1961"\w* \w the|strong="H3117"\w* \w morning|strong="H1242"\w*, making \w day|strong="H3117"\w* \w one|strong="H1961"\w*.\f + \fr 1:5 \ft It is significant that the “day” is measured from darkness to light, which is still the Jewish method of calculating days.\f*   
\p
\v 6 God said, “\w Let|strong="H1961"\w* \w there|strong="H1961"\w* \w be|strong="H1961"\w* \w an|strong="H1961"\w* \w expanse|strong="H7549"\w*\f + \fr 1:6 \ft “Expanse.” Older translations have often rendered this word as “firmament,” borrowing from the Latin “firmamentum.” That this referred to some ancient belief that the sky was like a dome of hammered metal, and therefore a tangible physical object, has now been shown to be mistaken. In fact, Latin translations from the sixteenth and seventeenth centuries usually use the word “expansionem.”\f* \w in|strong="H8432"\w* \w the|strong="H8432"\w* \w middle|strong="H8432"\w* \w of|strong="H4325"\w* \w the|strong="H8432"\w* \w waters|strong="H4325"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* divide \w the|strong="H8432"\w* \w waters|strong="H4325"\w*.”  
\v 7 \w So|strong="H3651"\w* God \w made|strong="H6213"\w* \w an|strong="H6213"\w* \w expanse|strong="H7549"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* divide \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w waters|strong="H4325"\w* \w that|strong="H3651"\w* \w were|strong="H1961"\w* \w above|strong="H5921"\w* \w from|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w waters|strong="H4325"\w* \w that|strong="H3651"\w* \w were|strong="H1961"\w* \w below|strong="H8478"\w*. \w And|strong="H6213"\w* \w that|strong="H3651"\w*'s \w what|strong="H6213"\w* \w happened|strong="H1961"\w*.  
