\v 1 \w The|strong="H3605"\w* \w serpent|strong="H5175"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* \w more|strong="H3808"\w* cunning \w than|strong="H3808"\w* \w any|strong="H3605"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w other|strong="H3605"\w* \w wild|strong="H7704"\w* \w animals|strong="H2416"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w Lord|strong="H3068"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w had|strong="H3068"\w* \w made|strong="H6213"\w*. \w He|strong="H3588"\w* asked Eve, “\w Did|strong="H6213"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w* really say \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w you|strong="H3588"\w* \w can|strong="H6213"\w*'t eat \w fruit|strong="H3605"\w* \w from|strong="H3068"\w* \w every|strong="H3605"\w*\f + \fr 3:1 \ft “Every”: the word could also be translated “any,” however this would then mean that the serpent was suggesting that God had told Adam and Eve not to eat fruit from any tree in the garden, which seems less likely.\f* \w tree|strong="H6086"\w* \w in|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w garden|strong="H1588"\w*?”   
