\v 4 \w There|strong="H1961"\w* \w were|strong="H1961"\w* \w giants|strong="H5303"\w*\f + \fr 6:4 \ft “Giants”: literally, “Nephelim.” This word is translated “giants” in the Septuagint. However, some take the word to be based on the Hebrew word “fallen.” These “giants” are also referenced later (see \xt Numbers 13:33\ft ). In Symmachus' Greek translation he renders “Nephelim” as “the violent ones.”\f* \w on|strong="H3117"\w* earth \w in|strong="H3117"\w* \w those|strong="H1992"\w* \w days|strong="H3117"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w also|strong="H1571"\w* \w later|strong="H1961"\w* \w on|strong="H3117"\w*. \w They|strong="H1992"\w* \w were|strong="H1961"\w* \w born|strong="H3205"\w* \w after|strong="H1961"\w* \w the|strong="H3205"\w* \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* God slept \w with|strong="H3117"\w* \w the|strong="H3205"\w* \w daughters|strong="H1323"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w these|strong="H1992"\w* \w people|strong="H1121"\w*. \w Their|strong="H1992"\w* \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* \w became|strong="H3205"\w* \w the|strong="H3205"\w* \w great|strong="H1368"\w* \w warriors|strong="H1368"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w famous|strong="H8034"\w* \w men|strong="H1368"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w ancient|strong="H5769"\w* \w times|strong="H3117"\w*.   
