\p
\v 3 They said \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w one|strong="H1961"\w* \w another|strong="H7453"\w*, “\w Come|strong="H1961"\w* \w on|strong="H1961"\w*, \w let|strong="H1961"\w*'s \w make|strong="H3835"\w* some \w bricks|strong="H3843"\w* \w and|strong="H7453"\w* bake \w them|strong="H8313"\w* \w with|strong="H8313"\w* \w fire|strong="H8316"\w*.” (They \w used|strong="H1961"\w* \w brick|strong="H3843"\w* instead \w of|strong="H2563"\w* stone, \w and|strong="H7453"\w* \w tar|strong="H2564"\w* instead \w of|strong="H2563"\w* cement).\f + \fr 11:3 \ft This was because in the Babylonian plain there was no stone to use for buildings.\f*  
\v 4 \w Then|strong="H6213"\w* \w they|strong="H5921"\w* said, “\w Now|strong="H5921"\w* let's \w build|strong="H1129"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w city|strong="H5892"\w* \w for|strong="H5921"\w* \w ourselves|strong="H1129"\w* \w with|strong="H6213"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w tower|strong="H4026"\w* \w whose|strong="H8034"\w* \w top|strong="H7218"\w* reaches \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w heavens|strong="H8064"\w*. \w That|strong="H3605"\w* \w way|strong="H6440"\w* \w we|strong="H3068"\w*'ll gain \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w great|strong="H6213"\w* \w reputation|strong="H8034"\w* \w and|strong="H8064"\w* \w we|strong="H3068"\w* won't end \w up|strong="H1129"\w* \w being|strong="H8034"\w* \w scattered|strong="H6327"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w over|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* world.”   
